01:37:42.233 --> 01:37:45.611
- Got everybody all worried.
- Well, I finished school.

01:37:45.778 --> 01:37:46.987
I got my master's
in political science.

01:37:47.154 --> 01:37:50.115
Hey! That's what I'm talking about.

01:37:50.282 --> 01:37:52.576
Get that education.

01:37:52.743 --> 01:37:56.747
There he is!
Well, I'm gonna let you all to it.

01:37:56.914 --> 01:37:59.250
Ain't no need for that, Carter.

01:38:01.001 --> 01:38:04.713
- Hey, Dad.
- Get out of here, Louis.

01:38:07.800 --> 01:38:11.804
- Dad...
- I said leave.

01:38:20.479 --> 01:38:22.189
Keep doing what you doing.

01:38:24.733 --> 01:38:27.820
Thank you, Uncle Carter.

01:38:30.072 --> 01:38:33.534
Why you do that? Huh?
That was wrong.

01:38:33.701 --> 01:38:36.412
That boy's hurting, too. He's just
trying to get his act together.

01:38:36.579 --> 01:38:38.789
He should be hurting, Carter.

01:38:39.790 --> 01:38:42.751
Boy didn't even go
to his own brother's funeral.

01:38:43.752 --> 01:38:48.632
He's full of shit is what he is.
He ain't doing nothing right.

01:38:48.799 --> 01:38:51.635
He just got his master's!
What more you want him to do?

01:38:51.802 --> 01:38:56.056
Every gray hair I have
is 'cause of that boy.

01:39:07.860 --> 01:39:09.945
<i>The years started to drift by, </i>

01:39:10.112 --> 01:39:13.699
<i>but the pain in my heart
never went away.</i>

01:39:22.875 --> 01:39:27.087
<i>Through it all,
Louis and I never spoke.</i>

01:39:31.508 --> 01:39:36.138
<i>As we are a nation under God,
so I am sworn...</i>

01:39:56.575 --> 01:39:57.826
<i>Half of our
oil is now imported...</i>

01:39:57.993 --> 01:40:00.037
<i>It is a crisis that strikes
at the very hear':</i>

01:40:00.204 --> 01:40:02.456
<i>and soul and spirit
of our national will.</i>

01:40:02.623 --> 01:40:04.291
<i>- I feel one coming now.
- Not to worry.</i>

01:40:04.458 --> 01:40:06.126
<i>Two of you,
stay home until you feel better.</i>

01:40:06.293 --> 01:40:10.589
<i>OK, Barn, I'll stay.
But I ain't never gonna feel no better.</i>

01:40:19.139 --> 01:40:22.976
<i>In our district alone,
we have nine percent unemployment.</i>

01:40:23.143 --> 01:40:25.771
<i>In the country at large, 14 percent
are living below the poverty line.</i>

01:40:25.938 --> 01:40:29.149
<i>Sixty percent of those
are either black or Hispanic.</i>

01:40:29.316 --> 01:40:31.985
<i>Now, if I'm voted to Congress,
reducing those figures is gonna be</i>

01:40:32.152 --> 01:40:35.280
one of my primary objectives.

01:40:38.826 --> 01:40:40.327
Yeah?

01:40:40.494 --> 01:40:42.246
Oh, hey.

01:40:42.413 --> 01:40:44.164
Thanks for getting back to me.

01:40:48.293 --> 01:40:50.087
How much did he lose by?

01:40:52.840 --> 01:40:55.926
Really?

01:40:56.093 --> 01:40:57.720
All right, then.

01:40:57.886 --> 01:40:59.680
I appreciate it.

01:41:04.643 --> 01:41:06.562
No, he didn't win.

01:41:08.439 --> 01:41:10.691
I think you should call him.

01:41:12.985 --> 01:41:15.988
Right after Charlie passed,

01:41:16.155 --> 01:41:18.657
Louis came over
and paid me a visit.

01:41:18.824 --> 01:41:20.451
Hmm.

01:41:22.035 --> 01:41:25.456
He found me on the kitchen floor.

01:41:25.622 --> 01:41:27.875
I had passed out.

01:41:28.041 --> 01:41:30.043
Drunk.

01:41:30.210 --> 01:41:33.922
I'd gone to the bathroom
all over myself.

01:41:37.050 --> 01:41:39.428
He's the one that cleaned me up.

01:41:42.765 --> 01:41:46.727
And then he told me
I was the best mother

01:41:46.894 --> 01:41:49.688
anybody could ever want.

01:41:52.983 --> 01:41:55.277
I think, about now...

01:41:57.070 --> 01:41:59.948
...he'd want to hear from his daddy.

01:42:01.867 --> 01:42:03.994
I think you ought to call him.

01:42:08.957 --> 01:42:10.626
Mm-hm.

01:42:10.793 --> 01:42:11.794
Cecil?

01:42:14.254 --> 01:42:15.255
Cecil?

01:42:15.422 --> 01:42:18.175
Yes, sir, Mr. President.

01:42:18.342 --> 01:42:20.177
You stay there, I'm coming to you.

01:42:20.344 --> 01:42:23.889
I... have a...

01:42:24.056 --> 01:42:26.683
...secret mission for you.

01:42:26.850 --> 01:42:28.143
Yes, sir.

01:42:28.310 --> 01:42:30.604
I like to send people
money when they write me

01:42:30.771 --> 01:42:32.940
about their financial problems,

01:42:33.106 --> 01:42:37.110
but my staff has been
trying to get me to stop.

01:42:37.277 --> 01:42:41.031
You think you could
help me to keep this going?

01:42:41.198 --> 01:42:43.951
Absolutely, Mr. President.

01:42:44.117 --> 01:42:46.703
Well, I appreciate
your help with this.

01:42:46.870 --> 01:42:49.581
And, please, don't tell Nancy.

01:42:49.748 --> 01:42:51.500
Of course not.

01:42:55.337 --> 01:42:58.423
- Morning, Cecil.
- Morning, Mr. Warner.

01:43:02.845 --> 01:43:04.638
May I sit down?

01:43:13.313 --> 01:43:16.692
I've been here
for over 20 years now.

01:43:19.653 --> 01:43:24.491
For all that time,
the black help

01:43:24.658 --> 01:43:28.954
has been paid a smaller salary
than the white help.

01:43:30.914 --> 01:43:34.418
And I just don't think
that's right, Mr. Warner.

01:43:36.670 --> 01:43:42.301
There are black housemen
who should be engineers by now.

01:43:43.677 --> 01:43:46.805
They should've been promoted
years ago.

01:43:49.308 --> 01:43:51.101
You think so?

01:43:53.979 --> 01:43:59.651
I'm gonna have to be paid
the same as the white help,

01:43:59.818 --> 01:44:03.071
or I'm gonna have to move on.

01:44:04.781 --> 01:44:07.242
I guess you'll be moving on then.

01:44:11.371 --> 01:44:14.666
I told the president
that you'd say that.

01:44:16.460 --> 01:44:21.340
He told me to tell you
to take this up with him, personally.

01:44:25.677 --> 01:44:27.095
Excuse me.

01:44:35.771 --> 01:44:38.315
I'm not comfortable
with all the foreign policy hawks

01:44:38.482 --> 01:44:40.025
surrounding Ronnie, Jim.

01:44:40.192 --> 01:44:44.363
We need more moderates on his staff.
And a summit with the Russians.

01:44:44.529 --> 01:44:46.698
Ronnie has to meet
with them face to face

01:44:46.865 --> 01:44:48.200
if we're ever
going to thaw this ice.

01:44:48.367 --> 01:44:50.869
- Cecil.
- Yes, Mrs. Reagan?

01:44:51.036 --> 01:44:53.705
We will talk, Jim. Yes.

01:44:53.872 --> 01:44:55.540
Yes, ma'am?

01:44:55.707 --> 01:44:57.960
You're very popular around here.

01:44:58.126 --> 01:45:02.547
Everyone says you're the man
that got them raises and promotions.

01:45:02.714 --> 01:45:06.426
- I had no idea.
- I wish I could take credit for that.

01:45:07.177 --> 01:45:09.763
I'd like to invite you
to the State Dinner next week.

01:45:09.930 --> 01:45:12.307
- I'm gonna be there, Mrs. Reagan.
- No.

01:45:12.474 --> 01:45:17.229
Not as a... Not as a butler, Cecil.
I'm inviting you as a guest.

01:45:18.188 --> 01:45:21.358
But the president prefers
for me to serve him personally.

01:45:22.359 --> 01:45:25.404
Don't you worry about, Ronnie.
I'll take care of that.

01:45:26.279 --> 01:45:29.950
So we'll see you next week.
You and your wife.

01:45:30.117 --> 01:45:31.952
My Wife?

01:45:34.955 --> 01:45:37.916
It's... It's Gloria, yes?

01:45:38.083 --> 01:45:40.627
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes.

01:45:42.754 --> 01:45:44.089
Hmm.

01:45:56.935 --> 01:45:58.770
Here's the Entrance Hall.

01:46:03.108 --> 01:46:04.860
Beautiful.

01:46:20.083 --> 01:46:22.711
Can I get you a glass
of champagne, Mr. Gaines?

01:46:22.878 --> 01:46:26.715
- Shut up.
- Right.

01:46:28.717 --> 01:46:30.343
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:46:30.510 --> 01:46:33.972
the President and First Lady
of the United States.

01:46:55.285 --> 01:46:58.997
<i>It was different sitting
at the table instead of serving it.</i>

01:46:59.164 --> 01:47:00.582
<i>Real different.</i>

01:47:02.000 --> 01:47:06.630
<i>I could see the two faces
the butlers wore to survive.</i>

01:47:08.090 --> 01:47:12.385
<i>And I knew I'd lived my life
with those same two faces.</i>

01:47:18.934 --> 01:47:24.189
<i>Gloria looked so happy,
but I didn't feel the same way.</i>

01:47:24.356 --> 01:47:28.276
<i>I guess I wished we were there
for real instead of for show.</i>

01:47:38.703 --> 01:47:41.289
I think that's bon appétit, everybody.

01:47:41.456 --> 01:47:42.833
You black mother...

01:47:48.797 --> 01:47:53.009
I want to make myself clear
on this issue.

01:47:54.803 --> 01:48:01.226
If Congress passes sanctions
against South Africa,

01:48:01.393 --> 01:48:05.689
I will be forced to
veto those sanctions.

01:48:05.856 --> 01:48:10.026
Well, Mr. President, we feel
that that would be a major mistake.

01:48:10.193 --> 01:48:13.905
The brutal repression
of South African black citizens

01:48:14.072 --> 01:48:16.867
makes this no longer
a foreign policy issue,

01:48:17.033 --> 01:48:20.620
but a United States racial issue.

01:48:20.787 --> 01:48:23.540
We're senators
from your own party.

01:48:23.707 --> 01:48:25.667
That's why we feel so comfortable
in letting you know

01:48:25.834 --> 01:48:28.879
that South Africa
is a human rights disaster.

01:48:29.045 --> 01:48:32.591
Black people are
being beaten, tortured,

01:48:32.757 --> 01:48:34.759
gunned down
in the middle of the street.

01:48:34.926 --> 01:48:38.680
Americans see all this on TV,
they're horrified by apartheid.

01:48:38.847 --> 01:48:41.558
I've made my decision.

01:48:41.725 --> 01:48:46.188
Mr. President, your reputation
as a world leader is at stake.

01:48:46.354 --> 01:48:48.732
United States of America needs to be

01:48:48.899 --> 01:48:51.067
on the right side of history
on the race issue.

01:48:51.234 --> 01:48:52.819
I say again.

01:48:54.237 --> 01:48:58.158
If Congress passes this bill,

01:48:58.325 --> 01:49:00.994
I Will veto it.

01:49:01.161 --> 01:49:02.829
Period.

01:49:12.297 --> 01:49:16.134
What? You reading now?

01:49:16.301 --> 01:49:18.720
Get up and do the dishes
'fore I shoot your little ass.

01:49:32.567 --> 01:49:36.404
<i>Nothing seemed right to me
after that State Dinner.</i>

01:49:36.571 --> 01:49:38.782
<i>Got all confused.</i>

01:50:05.517 --> 01:50:08.436
<i>They had started writing books</i>

01:50:08.603 --> 01:50:12.899
<i>about everything Louis
and his friends had done.</i>

01:50:18.321 --> 01:50:20.657
<i>Louis was never a criminal.</i>

01:50:24.536 --> 01:50:27.872
<i>He was a hero, </i>

01:50:28.039 --> 01:50:31.376
<i>fighting to save
the soul of our country.</i>

01:50:42.554 --> 01:50:45.390
- Would you like a cookie?
- Thank you, sir.

01:50:45.557 --> 01:50:47.350
- Cookies.
- Thank you.

01:50:47.517 --> 01:50:48.935
Cookie?

01:50:49.102 --> 01:50:51.062
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

01:50:51.229 --> 01:50:52.689
Thank you.

01:50:52.856 --> 01:50:53.982
Cookie?

01:51:08.788 --> 01:51:14.044
<i>I had always loved sewing.
But just felt different now.</i>

01:51:17.505 --> 01:51:21.968
<i>I didn't know that an old man
could feel so lost.</i>

01:51:22.886 --> 01:51:24.679
<i>That's how I felt.</i>

01:51:25.972 --> 01:51:27.891
<i>That's how I felt.</i>

01:51:34.647 --> 01:51:36.733
<i>Americans always turned</i>

01:51:36.900 --> 01:51:41.780
<i>a blind eye to what we'd done
to our own.</i>

01:51:41.946 --> 01:51:45.742
<i>We look out to the world
and judge.</i>

01:51:45.909 --> 01:51:48.870
<i>We hear about
the concentration camps, </i>

01:51:49.037 --> 01:51:54.000
<i>but these camps went on
for 200 years</i>

01:51:54.167 --> 01:51:56.920
<i>right here in America.</i>

01:52:09.140 --> 01:52:11.267
Buried my daddy right over there.

01:52:15.563 --> 01:52:19.609
My mama would've been
right proud of me,

01:52:19.776 --> 01:52:22.570
being with a man like you's.

01:52:22.737 --> 01:52:26.116
Taking such good care of me
all of these years.

01:52:29.077 --> 01:52:31.121
I love you, Cecil Gaines.

01:52:33.665 --> 01:52:36.000
I love you more, Gloria.

01:52:48.471 --> 01:52:51.891
Are you sure about this?

01:52:52.058 --> 01:52:53.810
Yes, sir.

01:52:53.977 --> 01:52:58.815
I just want to be the one
to tell you first, that's all.

01:52:58.982 --> 01:53:01.568
But you're the best butler here.

01:53:01.734 --> 01:53:04.195
You're like family, Cecil.

01:53:06.197 --> 01:53:08.783
Been an honor serving you.

01:53:08.950 --> 01:53:13.163
Well, not just for me,
I'm sure I speak for all the presidents

01:53:13.329 --> 01:53:17.500
when I say that you've
served your country well.

01:53:19.794 --> 01:53:21.546
Thank you, Mr. President.

01:53:26.468 --> 01:53:27.927
Cecil?

01:53:30.054 --> 01:53:32.682
This whole civil rights issue...

01:53:36.311 --> 01:53:39.439
I sometimes fear I'm...

01:53:39.606 --> 01:53:42.150
on the wrong side of it,
that I'm...

01:53:43.276 --> 01:53:45.361
...just wrong.

01:53:45.528 --> 01:53:49.449
Sometimes I think I'm just
scared of what it really means.

01:53:51.743 --> 01:53:54.579
But I'm trying not to be
so scared anymore.

01:53:55.371 --> 01:53:57.999
<i>- Who do we want to free?!
- Mandela!</i>

01:53:58.166 --> 01:53:59.375
When do we want him free?

01:53:59.542 --> 01:54:00.877
- Now!
- Free Mandela!

01:54:01.044 --> 01:54:05.548
Twenty years ago, we marched
in this country for our rights.

01:54:07.717 --> 01:54:11.638
Today, we march to free
the people of South Africa.

01:54:11.804 --> 01:54:13.181
Yeah!

01:54:13.348 --> 01:54:17.894
Ronald Reagan has attacked or dismantled
every civil rights program

01:54:18.061 --> 01:54:20.063
that has ever been put in place.

01:54:20.230 --> 01:54:21.606
- Yeah!
- Right!

01:54:21.773 --> 01:54:25.443
Aiding the oppression of black South
Africans is absolutely consistent

01:54:25.610 --> 01:54:29.113
with his policies on race issues.
Am I right?

01:54:29.280 --> 01:54:31.699
- Am I right?
- Yes!

01:54:33.701 --> 01:54:35.578
Hold on, hold on.

01:54:37.080 --> 01:54:39.832
Excuse me. Steven?
Where's Steven?

01:54:39.999 --> 01:54:41.834
- Free Mandela!
- Free Mandela, y'all!

01:54:42.001 --> 01:54:43.836
Free Mandela!

01:54:45.588 --> 01:54:50.426
Free Mandela!
Free Mandela! Free Mandela!

01:55:00.937 --> 01:55:03.189
Hi, Dad.

01:55:03.356 --> 01:55:05.692
Hi, Louis.

01:55:07.443 --> 01:55:10.446
What are you doing here?

01:55:15.868 --> 01:55:18.580
I came here to protest with you.

01:55:21.708 --> 01:55:24.294
You'll get arrested, Dad.
You'll lose your job.

01:55:26.629 --> 01:55:28.715
I lost you.

01:55:32.635 --> 01:55:34.470
I'm sorry.

01:55:44.647 --> 01:55:47.483
I'm sorry, son.

01:56:06.711 --> 01:56:10.423
Don't worry, Dad, we'll be
out of here in a few hours.

01:56:10.590 --> 01:56:12.800
Who said I was worried?

01:56:17.555 --> 01:56:21.976
<i>After going to jail,
I thought I'd seen it all.</i>

01:56:22.352 --> 01:56:26.105
- You OK, Daddy?
- Yeah, no, no, no. I'm good.

01:56:26.272 --> 01:56:29.734
<i>But I never imagined I'd see...</i>

01:56:29.901 --> 01:56:31.986
<i>...a black man</i>

01:56:32.153 --> 01:56:37.075
<i>be a real contender for
the President of the United States.</i>

01:56:41.454 --> 01:56:43.498
Here we go.

01:56:43.665 --> 01:56:47.418
- It's that sweet corn.
- That corn look good.

01:57:00.390 --> 01:57:03.518
<i>Gloria and I would walk
to our polling place</i>

01:57:03.685 --> 01:57:08.731
<i>every night to see where
we'd be voting for Barack Obama.</i>

01:57:10.400 --> 01:57:14.529
<i>We'd just... stare at it, smile.</i>

01:57:20.368 --> 01:57:23.413
- You done?
- Pretty much.

01:57:23.579 --> 01:57:25.790
Good. Time to go.

01:57:27.291 --> 01:57:30.002
You done pretty good there.

01:57:30.169 --> 01:57:32.088
Thanks, honey.

01:57:33.423 --> 01:57:37.468
How come Louis' wife
named that child...

01:57:37.635 --> 01:57:40.471
- ...Shaquanda?
- Now, don't start that again.

01:57:40.638 --> 01:57:44.892
I ain't starting it, I just don't know
what kind of name that is.

01:57:45.059 --> 01:57:48.563
I mean, really! Shaquanda?

01:57:48.730 --> 01:57:50.732
I think she done that just to spite me.

01:57:50.898 --> 01:57:54.652
Ain't nobody
done nothing to spite you.

01:57:54.819 --> 01:57:56.738
Yes, she did.

01:57:58.531 --> 01:58:02.118
She a ugly little old girl, too.
That little pug nose.

01:58:02.285 --> 01:58:06.372
- I hope she grow out of it.
- Now, you need to stop that.

01:58:06.539 --> 01:58:08.416
- You know that ain't right.
- Don't you think

01:58:08.583 --> 01:58:10.460
she look a little like
Louis around the mouth?

01:58:10.626 --> 01:58:14.589
I think... she look just like you.

01:58:14.756 --> 01:58:16.591
- Like me?
- Yeah, so you need to...

01:58:16.758 --> 01:58:19.510
...you need
to stop talking about her.

01:58:19.677 --> 01:58:22.680
Let me look at her again,
then, real good.

01:58:25.141 --> 01:58:30.396
She do look a little bit like me.
She a pretty little thing.

01:58:31.731 --> 01:58:34.567
I guess I can put up
with the name Shaquanda.

01:58:36.152 --> 01:58:39.238
I forgot where I put my Bible.

01:58:39.405 --> 01:58:43.117
- You know I need my Bible.
- Mm-hm.

01:58:43.284 --> 01:58:46.871
- I think I left it in the bathroom.
- Why is Louis late?

01:58:48.289 --> 01:58:51.209
Boy gets elected to Congress...

01:58:51.375 --> 01:58:54.754
